text: Andriy Kis (born May 27, 1982 in Lviv) is a Ukrainian luger who has competed since 2003. Competing in two Winter Olympics, he earned his best finish of 14th in the men's doubles event at Turin in 2006. Kis's best finish at the FIL World Luge Championships in the men's double event was 14th twice (2008, 2009). His best finish at the FIL European Luge Championships was ninth in the men's doubles event at Sigulda in 2010. ==References== * 2006 luge men's doubles results * * ==External links== * Category:1982 births Category:Living people Category:Lugers at the 2006 Winter Olympics Category:Lugers at the 2010 Winter Olympics Category:Lugers at the 2014 Winter Olympics Category:Olympic lugers of Ukraine Category:Sportspeople from Lviv Category:Ukrainian male lugers
